              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>A <fr:link href="/jms-00KF/" title="Function" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KF/" display-uri="jms-00KF" type="local">function</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is said to be <html:em><html:strong>bijective</html:strong></html:em> or <html:em><html:strong>bijection</html:strong></html:em> whenever there exists a (necessarily unique) function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> (referred to as the <html:em><html:strong>inverse</html:strong></html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>) that is simultaneously a <fr:link href="/jms-00KS/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KS/" display-uri="jms-00KS" type="local">retraction</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="/jms-00KS/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KS/" display-uri="jms-00KS" type="local">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> in the sense that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f=\mathsf {id}_{A}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  g = \mathsf {id}_{B}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p><html:p>We will often write <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f^{-1}\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> for the inverse to a bijection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>23</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>To see that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> is unique, we fix any other <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g']]></fr:tex> that is simultaneously a <fr:link href="/jms-00KS/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KS/" display-uri="jms-00KS" type="local">retraction</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="/jms-00KS/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KS/" display-uri="jms-00KS" type="local">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> and show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g=g']]></fr:tex>:</html:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
    g &= \mathsf {id}_{A}\circ  g\\
    &= {\mathopen {}\left (g'\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}} \circ  g\\
    &= g'\circ {\mathopen {}\left (f\circ  g\right )\mathclose {}}\\
    &= g'\circ \mathsf {id}_{B}\\
    &= g'
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
