          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>section-retraction pair</html:strong></html:em> is defined to be a pair of <fr:link href="/jms-00KF/" title="Function" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KF/" display-uri="jms-00KF" type="local">functions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  B \to  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\circ  s =\mathsf {id}_{B}]]></fr:tex>. In this case, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> is referred to as a <html:em><html:strong>section</html:strong></html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> is referred to as a <html:em><html:strong>retraction</html:strong></html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
